{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f8820713-7695-4f15-aef1-b78b4bb00afc","content":"No worries — here's how to configure it. Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`command`/`args`** — Uses `dotnet run` to build and launch your project.\n- Your server must use **stdio transport** (not HTTP/SSE). If you're using the `ModelContextProtocol` NuGet package, ensure you call `.WithStdioServerTransport()` in your host builder.\n\nAfter saving, open the Copilot chat panel in agent mode — it will auto-discover and start your server.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b7a94e9d-4617-4f3d-9505-7e80dab16a75","outputTokens":241,"requestId":"AC06:2BC959:AE279F:DA0192:6A012D55"},"id":"351d680a-4189-478a-b27c-bffb8095b69f","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:14:05.500Z","parentId":"0c27ec98-4f5c-4bed-b1e4-b1e2ced515b7"}
